PROGRAM:

import java.util.Scanner;
public class vowels {
    public static void main(String[] args){
        System.out.println("Enter a ch: ");
        Scanner sc=new Scanner(System.in);
        char ch = sc.next().toLowerCase().charAt(0);
        if(Character.isLetter(ch)){
            if(ch =='a'||ch =='e'||ch =='i'||ch =='o'||ch =='u'){
            System.out.println( ch + " is a vowel.");}
            else{
                System.out.println( ch +" is a consonant.");
            }      
            }
        }
    }


OUTPUT:
Enter a ch: 
a
a is a vowel.
Enter a ch: 
k
k is a consonant.


DESCRIPTION:
This is a simple program to find a char whether it is a 'vowel' or 'consonant'.
if we enter the char in uppercase letter it coverts the char into lowercase letter and then it checks whether the char is 'vowel' or 'consonant' and prints the output.
